  "body": "Currently in React 16.8.6, we get this error when changing the state in a affected useEffect,\r\n```Invariant Violation: Maximum update depth exceeded. This can happen when a component repeatedly calls setState inside componentWillUpdate or componentDidUpdate. React limits the number of nested updates to prevent infinite loops.```\r\n\r\nNow it can of course happen also in useEffects and it could be nice to have this message updated mention something about the \"dangerous\" combination of useStates and useEffects.",
